<div class="text">
  <p>
    Welcome to <strong>ZBoiler</strong>.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>ZBoiler</strong> will help you get started on your next
    Python project by providing a simple user interface for specifying
    the basic features of your project, like package metadata and
    automated testing.  Once you have the basic details of your
    project entered, <strong>ZBoiler</strong> will generate all the
    boilerplate code you need and provide an easy to download tarball.
  </p>
  <img id="screenshot"
       alt="ZBoiler Screenshot"
       tal:attributes="src context/++resource++ui/images/Screenshot.png" />

  <p>
    So whenever you're ready, just
    <strong><a href="build.html"
       tal:attributes="href string:${context/@@absolute_url}/build.html">
      start building!
    </a></strong>
  </p>

  <p tal:condition="view/projectTemplates">
    Or get jump-started by using a project template:
  </p>
  <ul tal:condition="view/projectTemplates">
    <li tal:repeat="template view/projectTemplates">
      <strong>
        <a tal:attributes="href string:build.html?template=${template/name}"
         tal:content="template/title"></a>
      </strong> - <span tal:replace="template/description"/>
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>